definitions.definition: The act or event of returning home.
examples: His homecoming was saddened by the news of his mother's death the day before.

definitions.definition: In colleges and high schools , a tradition centred around a football game, a parade and the " coronation " of a Homecoming Queen .
examples: Many alumni come back for homecoming , and many freshmen are advised to flee.

subdefinitions.definition: Ellipsis of harvest homecoming , a traditional (street) party and/or dance near the start of the school year, at around fall mid-terms . It traditionally marks the start of harvest break , where students go home in autumn to harvest the crops on the family farms.

main_definition: The act or event of returning home.
secondary_definitions: ( Canada , US , also attributive ) In colleges and high schools , a tradition centred around a football game, a parade and the " coronation " of a Homecoming Queen .
